CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 6, 1945, pg. 8 reads: "Popular Couple United - Charming Nora Elizabeth Lee, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. William Lee of Homewood, and Julius Banks of Baltimore, were married Saturday, Sept. 29, in a quiet ceremony in Parish House of Corpus Christi Church, Homewood. Many out-of-town guests attended the nuptials.  Left to right: Charles Johnson of Boston, Mass.; Tommy Roberts, best man, Washington, D.C.; the groom and bride, Jerry Washington, maid of honor; Cleveland, Ohio, and Eva Ruth Greenlee, bridesmaid, of Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Full length group portrait of Julius Banks and Nora Elizabeth Lee Banks, standing in front of fireplace with crucifix
